<p><a name="Kids"></a><font face="Times New Roman, Times, serif" size="4"><b>Treating kids humanely</b></font><p>

<font face="Times New Roman, Times, serif" size="3">IN MY state, a group called Legal Aid of North Carolina is attempting to put an end to the practice of shackling some under-age children who appear in court.<p>
No child should be handcuffed, shackled, or bound and gagged while in a court of law (or anywhere else for that matter). I would like to encourage your readers to try to stop these abuses in their states.<br>
<b>Chuck Mann</b>, Greensboro, N.C.<p>
<font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2"><a href="#Top">Back to the top</a></font><br>
